<br>
Thoran's surprise that day in Crushbone when he, then in his higher 20's at the very least if not his 30's, first encountered Retlon Brenclog...<br>
<br>
Galadria's first trip alone to turn in orc belts in Kaladim - plodding down the path, head down, concentrating on remembering the turns and handy shortcuts, all of a sudden near stunned with a mighty dwarven blow to the head! Not all dwarves in Butcherblock are elven friends... there are sometimes bandits about who hate our race (not to mention want any money or valuables we carry) and they will kill you if they can. Luckily for Galadria she was not too far from one of the many guard posts and fled in time to duck past the doughty guards, who slew her attacker before she had time to catch her breath.<br>
<br>
Kemie's first taste of Oasis... conveyed there by an enchanter friend who had been a druid in a former life, she was shown the basics of the art of kiting and then left alone to try the tactics on a wandering caimen. He'd made it look SO simple! Poor Kemie was more than two-thirds dead and almost out of mana by the time the beast lay dead at her feet. She could only collapse in the sand, over-heated and exhausted, and far too vulnerable had any of the other beasties there come upon her while she recovered! I must confess she had to steel her will after hesitating long and hard, before she ever tried tackling the second!<br>
<br>
